  "description": [
    "Unify The South Balance The Budget And Save The Nation New Conservative Party In Dixie Is Urged As Means Of Whipping Radicals Unify the South balance the budget and save the nation writes a man from San Francisco California In a letter to the editor published in THE SHREVEPORT JOURNAL of Shreveport Louisiana recently this man said I firmly believe that if as few as four or five Southern States including Texas would unite and form a new Conserva tive Party or adopt the Mississippi vot ing plan of withholding their votes in the general election they could possibly swing the next presidential election in 1964 In his letter he also points out that Congress should reduce taxes by eight or nine billion dollars next year and at the same time balance the budget and quit living on borrowed money Letter To Newspaper This letter was written by J L Lott a former resident of Mississippi and here is what he says Editor Shreveport Journal Being a Mississippian by birth as well as a conservative American at heart prompts me to follow the political situa tion not only as it affects the South but the nation as a whole Therefore"
  ],
